This is annoying when you have two or more extensions that update their status bar items. E.g. status monitoring extensions as #28586 .

### Steps to reproduce
Have the following code in your extension
```
export function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
    const item = vscode.window.createStatusBarItem(vscode.StatusBarAlignment.Left);
    item.show();
    setInterval(() => {    
        item.text = 'Extension 1';
    }, 3000);

    const item2 = vscode.window.createStatusBarItem(vscode.StatusBarAlignment.Left);
    item2.show();
    setInterval(() => {    
        item2.text = 'Extension 2';
    }, 2000);
}
```

### Result
![statusbarelems-switching](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2239563/27734867-22468d58-5d9d-11e7-8d9f-17582f4c722f.gif)


### Expectation
Positioning of status bar items is kept the same at least during the same VS Code session.
